# =============================================================================
# R2R INTERCOMPANY RECONCILIATION ENGINE
# .github/CODEOWNERS
#
# What this file does:
#   Enforces mandatory Pull Request review for financially significant files.
#   When anyone modifies a listed file, GitHub automatically requests a
#   review from the designated owner before the change can be merged.
#
#   Why this matters for SOX:
#     config.yaml contains materiality thresholds, entity contacts, and
#     account code ranges that directly affect financial reporting.
#     Changing these parameters without review is equivalent to modifying
#     a financial system without change management approval.
#     CODEOWNERS enforces Segregation of Duties — the person making the
#     change cannot be the sole approver.
#
#   How it works:
#     Any Pull Request that modifies a listed file triggers an automatic
#     review request to the listed GitHub username.
#     The PR cannot be merged until that person approves it.
#     This creates an immutable audit trail in GitHub of:
#       - Who proposed the change
#       - Who reviewed and approved it
#       - Exactly what changed (line-by-line diff)
#       - When it was merged
#
#   To update the reviewer:
#     Replace @Data-KentC below with the GitHub username of the
#     designated Financial Controller or Compliance Officer.
#     This file itself requires a PR to change — enforcing the control.
#
#   Format:
#     <file pattern>    <GitHub username(s)>
#     Patterns use gitignore syntax.
#     Multiple owners: @username1 @username2
# =============================================================================

# ─── Financially significant configuration ──────────────────────────────────
# Any change to config.yaml requires review.
# config.yaml contains: materiality thresholds, entity contacts,
# account code ranges, LLM settings, escalation SLAs.
config.yaml                   @Data-KentC

# ─── Matching engine logic ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes to matching tiers require review — they affect STP rate and
# which transactions are classified as exceptions vs matched.
src/matching/exact.py         @Data-KentC
src/matching/tolerance.py     @Data-KentC
src/matching/subset_sum.py    @Data-KentC
src/matching/engine.py        @Data-KentC

# ─── Database schema ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Schema changes affect audit trail and data integrity.
src/persistence/models.py     @Data-KentC
src/persistence/database.py   @Data-KentC

# ─── GitHub Actions workflows ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Workflow changes could affect scheduling, permissions, or secret access.
.github/workflows/            @Data-KentC

# ─── This file itself ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changing CODEOWNERS requires approval — prevents bypassing the control.
.github/CODEOWNERS            @Data-KentC
